Text: As he says people, you CAN NOT remove the protection on files IF you dont HAVE THE LICENSE to play it in the first place

usually most sites saves the license to your computer (atleast the 2 sites I've tried). I tried another program to "re-record" the files, called Tunebite. If someone doesnt get this to work, try Tunebite instead

Two virus detectors detected a trojan
w32.trojan.gen

Works great on tracks I bought from Urge using latest Windows Media Player 11 and Windows Vista 32-bit!

nod32 picks up no viruses and MD5 Checksums match those on doom9 Forums. (In other words they 100% is no viruses in this!)

aero87 should get a decent scanner or at least realize that EXE Packers like UPX cause false positives on the lesser scanners.
